Altberg has also produced a documentary about the project (in Portuguese, no
subtitles):

In the book, Ana Maria Mauad, associate professor at the History Department of
Federal Fluminense University, reflects on the symbolism and timeless
character of the images:

> O mundo que conhecemos com essas imagens atravessa os tempos, reunindo
> passado e presente – os Rios de Machado, do conflito, da pacificação, da
> vida das pessoas comuns nas suas fascinantes excepcionalidades.

> The world we get to know with those images traverses time, uniting past and
> present – the “Rio de Janeiros” of Machado de Assis, of the conflict, of the
> pacification, of the life of common people in their fascinating
> exceptionalities.

